      sanskrit: "aparokṣajñānarahitajñānino'pi sādhāraṇayatnavato'pi manoharatī­ndriyāṇi|puruṣasya śarīrābhimāninaḥ| ko doṣastataḥ ? pramāthīni pramathanaśīlāni puruṣasya",
      ourRendering: "Even of a knower lacking direct knowledge, even of one making ordinary effort, the senses carry off the mind; of a man, one possessed of body-conceit. What is the fault therefrom? They are of churning nature, of the nature to churn the man.",
