      ourRendering: "Since the fault in the engagement of the senses has been established, therefore — of which ascetic, O mighty-armed, the senses are restrained from every side, by every kind of restraint, mental and the rest, restrained from the sense-objects, sound and the rest — his insight stands firm.",
      source: "data/sources/sanskrit/vedanta/shankara_gita_bhasya.txt (GRETIL: gretil/1_sanskr/6_sastra/3_phil/vedanta/bhgsbh_u.htm)"
