      ourRendering: "‘hi’ (since) — since it is thus, ‘therefore’. From every side, all of them, together with the mind. Addressing him ‘O mighty-armed’, He hints: since you are able to ward off every foe, you are able also to ward off the foe that is the senses. The rest is clear. ‘Of him’ refers to both the accomplished one and the aspirant, since the senses’ restraint, being for the sthita-prajña a mark and for the seeker of release a means to insight, is to be summed up.",
